{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FgWtfiepJoqsgnheMjmdPg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the issue clearly now. The current probe configuration has very tight settings that are likely causing failures:\n\n**Liveness probe:**\n- `initialDelaySeconds: 15` - MongoDB likely hasn't started authentication yet in 15 seconds\n- `timeoutSeconds: 1` - mongosh command very likely takes more than 1 second to complete\n- `failureThreshold: 2` - Only 2 failures allowed before restart\n\n**Readiness probe:**\n- `initialDelaySeconds: 5` - Way too short for MongoDB to be ready\n- `timeoutSeconds: 1` - mongosh command very likely takes more than 1 second\n- `failureThreshold: 2` - Only 2 failures allowed\n\nComparing this to the original working configuration from the last-applied-configuration annotation shows a dramatic difference: the liveness probe had `initialDelaySeconds: 60`, `timeoutSeconds: 5`, and `failureThreshold: 10`, while readiness had `initialDelaySeconds: 30`, `timeoutSeconds: 5`, and `failureThreshold: 6`. The current generation 3 values are severely misconfigured with initial delays that are far too short and timeout windows that don't give mongosh enough time to execute.\n\nMongoDB needs significant startup time to initialize the daemon, set up the replica set, and handle authentication. The readiness probe kicks in at just 5 seconds with only a 1-second window and 2 allowed failures, which means the pod gets marked not ready almost immediately. The liveness probe follows at 15 seconds with the same tight constraints, and if MongoDB still isn't responding in that 1-second window, the container gets killed and restarted. Looking at the pod timeline, they've only been running 8-10 seconds, so they haven't had a chance to fully initialize yet.\n\nThe original configuration had much more reasonable values—60 seconds initial delay for liveness with 5-second timeouts and 10 allowed failures, plus 30 seconds for readiness with 5-second timeouts and 6 allowed failures. Someone changed these to the current aggressive settings, which is why the pods keep failing. I need to patch the StatefulSet back to those original working probe values.\n\nI should also verify the admin-secret credentials are correct and check the MongoDB configuration and pod events to understand what's actually failing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2263,"cache_read_input_tokens":28318,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2263},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"87554b50-6df7-40da-ad69-f55fa4eac1b5","uuid":"b5069fd6-8bdd-48e6-8a92-f62ce6a4eb60","request_id":"req_011Ccf5KWZ5QbrxPYE1gJLAD"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FgWtfiepJoqsgnheMjmdPg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is clear: the current probes have been tightened to aggressive values that can't work:\n- `timeoutSeconds: 1` (mongosh auth takes longer than 1s)\n- `initialDelaySeconds: 5/15` (MongoDB hasn't started yet)\n- `failureThreshold: 2` (almost no tolerance)\n\nThe original working values from the `last-applied-configuration` annotation show what they should be. Let me check events and then patch the StatefulSet."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2263,"cache_read_input_tokens":28318,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2263},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"87554b50-6df7-40da-ad69-f55fa4eac1b5","uuid":"540088e7-676f-4521-9d00-a9a3169f7e52","request_id":"req_011Ccf5KWZ5QbrxPYE1gJLAD"}
